
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to dynamically add nodes to a specific destination node. It uses the [add] slot to append nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node's [params] child into the destination node specified by the expression [./0/-/add/*]. This allows for flexible manipulation of the node structure by adding children nodes from a specified source.
add:x:./0/-/add/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/params
